<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Cookies</h1>

<p class="govuk-body">The service currently known as help to buy healthy food will put small files known as 'cookies'
    onto your computer.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">These cookies are used to help us:</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>keep track of the information you give us during your application</li>
    <li>remember which language you want to view the service in</li>
    <li>understand how you use the service, so we can make improvements</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body">Find out <a class="govuk-link" href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/online/cookies/">how to
    manage cookies on the Information Commissioners' website.</a></p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Google Analytics cookie</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">We use Google Analytics to collect information about how you use the service. This information
    helps us to make improvements.</p>

<p class="govuk-body">The Google analytics cookie collects and stores information about:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>the pages you visit - how long you spend on each page</li>
    <li>how you got to the service</li>
    <li>what you click on while you are using the service</li>
</ul>

